	  <p>To anhydrous AlCl<sub>3</sub> (27.35 g, 205 mmol) and anisole (24.11 g, 223 mmol) in dry chloroform (300 mL) 2-bromobenzeneacetyl chloride [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="B1-molbank-2002-M290">1</xref>] (43.4 g, 186 mmol) in dry chloroform (100 mL) was added over 30 min at 0 &#xB0;C and stirred at ambient temperature for 15 h. 2 N HCl (100 mL) was added, and the mixture was extracted with CH<sub>2</sub>Cl<sub>2</sub> (2 x 100 mL). The combined organic layer was washed with 2 N HCl (2 x 250 mL), water (2 x 250 mL), satd. NaHCO<sub>3</sub> (2 x 200 mL) and brine (200 mL), dried over Na<sub>2</sub>SO<sub>4</sub>, filtered and concentrated in vacuo. The residue was recrystallized from MeOH (50 mL). Yield: colorless crystals (51.3 g, 90%), mp. 87.5 - 88.5 &#xB0;C.</p>
      <p>TLC: petroleum ether : EtOAc = 80 : 20, R<sub>f</sub> = 0.3.</p>
      <p>Anal. Calcd for C<sub>15</sub>H<sub>31</sub>BrO: C, 59.04; H, 4.29. Found: C, 58.98; H, 4.33.</p>
      <p><sup>1</sup>H NMR (CDCl<sub>3</sub>): d 8.04 (d, J = 9.5 Hz, 2H), 7.60 (d, J = 9.5 Hz, 1H), 7.32 - 7.10 (m, 5H), 6.97 (d, J = 9.5 Hz, 2H), 4.40 (s, 2H), 3.88 (s, 3H).</p>
      <p><sup>13</sup>C NMR (CDCl<sub>3</sub>): d 194.8 (s), 163.6 (s), 135.2 (s), 132.6 (d), 131.6 (d), 130.6 (d), 129.6 (s), 128.5 (d), 127.4 (d), 125.0 (s), 113.8 (d), 55.4 (q), 45.3 (t).</p>
